The paper focuses on channel-state information and communication systems, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of massive MIMO technology also suggests a potential fit with multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed algorithm for acquiring reliable CSIT involves compressive sampling, which could be relevant to computer science and information retrieval (cs.COM).
